2. cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses optimizing transmission power to maximize frequency reuse. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible category as the paper deals with caching video content. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possible category as the paper discusses collaboration between wireless devices. 
5. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also a possible category as the paper discusses a distributed caching policy.
